# Task 1: Exploring and Visualizing a Simple Dataset

## Objective
To understand how to read, summarize, and visualize a dataset using Python libraries.

## Dataset
The Iris Dataset was used for this task. It contains flower measurements such as sepal length, sepal width, petal length, and petal width.

## Approach
- Loaded the dataset using Pandas
- Explored the dataset structure using `.shape`, `.columns`, and `.head()`
- Performed basic summarization
- Created scatter plots, histograms, and box plots
- Used Matplotlib and Seaborn for visualizations

## Results and Insights
The analysis revealed relationships between flower measurements and showed clear distribution patterns. Visualizations also helped detect variation and possible outliers.

## Skills Applied
- Data loading and inspection
- Data summarization
- Visualization with Matplotlib and Seaborn
